The commission of inquiry into state capture continues on Thursday. Thobani Mnyandu from MNS Attorneys will start with his testimony at the Zondo Commission. JOHANNESBURG - The commission of inquiry into state capture continues on Thursday. Thobani Mnyandu from MNS Attorneys will start with his testimony at the Zondo Commission. READ: Transnet employee accuses Molefe of 'steamrolling decisions' Mnyandu's colleague, Tshiamo Sedumedi testified before the commission on Wednesday, revealing flaws in the Transnet procurement system. Sedumedi also shared details about a report submitted to Transnet after investigations into tender irregularities. The law firm conducted the investigations last year.